Package tr.edu.ku.devnull.needforspear.Viewmodel.GameLogicHandlers

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    BackgroundHandler
    BackgroundHandler is Controller Design Pattern to achieve MVVM Design on displaying background image.
    BuildModeHandler
    BuildModeHandler computes the operations related to the building mode such as creating obstacle instances and setting their locations
    CollisionHandler
    CollisionHandler performs computations for detecting collisions among different types of game objects
    CollisionHandlerTest  
    HollowPurpleHandler
    Handler for HollowPurpleSpell.
    KeyDispatcher
    KeyDispatcher class is implemented for listening the key events and taking action accordingly.
    MagicalHexHandler
    Handler for the Magical Hex.
    MainMenuHandler
    MainMenuHandler is Controller Design Pattern to achieve MVVM Design on main menu actions.
    MapHandler
    MapHandler is Controller Design Pattern to achieve MVVM Design on map actions.
    MovementHandler
    This class does the location calculations for movements of sphere, obstacles and NoblePhantasm.
    PlayerLivesHandler
    This class does the computations to calculate lives of the player using observer pattern
    PlayerScoreHandler
    PlayerScoreHandler is a class that contains information regarding the player and their score and updates it accordingly.
    SaveLoadHandler
    SaveLoadHandler is Controller Design Pattern to achieve MVVM Design on map loading actions.
    SpellHandler
    SpellHandler computes the operations related to spells such as assigning them to giftObstacles
    SwitchModeHandler
    Using controller pattern to handle switching to running mode with an observer.
